The General Overseer of Mountain of Fire and Miracles Ministries (MFM), Dr Daniel Okukoya, has counselled Nigerians not to panic over the COVID-19 pandemic. Olukoya, who disclosed this in a statement by his Media Office, said: “I urge all Christians and men of faith, irrespective of denomination and religion to pray the following prayers to receive protection and healing from the virus and other pestilence likely to come this year.”  Quoting from 3John 1:2, he advised : “These prayers should be done along with the officially released hygiene and sanitation protocols.” He assured the federal and state governments were doing so much to contain the virus.